<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/7575> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #7575" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/5> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Pr. 104. Monetalis. In MRR 2.443, and Index, 581, refer also to Crawford, RRC 1.306-307, no. 292, 113 or 112 B.C. Note Crawford's opposing discussion of L. R. Taylor, RVA 39, on the arrangement and meaning of the voting scenes.\n" .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/3558> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #3558" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "As governor of Sicily, he carried out senatorial instructions to investigate and set free citizens of allied states who were held in slavery. Many of the slaves conspired and revolted, balked his attempt to take Murgantia, and occupied much of the island (Diod. 36.3-6; Dio 27, fr. 93.1-3)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/3557> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #3557" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Diod. and Dio use the terms {Gr} and {Gr}, respectively, to describe Nerva's command in Sicily; and Wehrman, FP, lists him as Pr. in 104. The possibility that he was Pr. in 105 and Propraetor in 104 is not excluded." .
